		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We consider loss functions for multiclass prediction problems. We show when a multiclass loss can be expressed as a &quot;proper composite loss&quot;, which is the composition of a proper loss and a link function. We extend existing results for binary losses to multiclass losses. We determine the stationarity condition, Breg-man representation, order-sensitivity, existence and uniqueness of the composite representation for multiclass losses. We subsume existing results on &quot;classifica-tion calibration&quot; by relating it to properness and show that the simple integral representation for binary proper losses can not be extended to multiclass losses.</p>
			</abstract>
